# <type>(<scope>): <subject>
#
# Types:
#   feat     ✨ new feature
#   fix      🐛 bug fix
#   refactor ♻️ code change (no behavior change)
#   perf     ⚡ performance improvement
#   docs     📝 documentation only
#   style    💄 formatting, missing semi colons, etc
#   test     ✅ adding or fixing tests
#   chore    🔧 maintenance, tooling
#   build    📦 build system or dependencies
#   ci       🤖 CI/CD changes
#   revert   ⏪ revert commit
#
# Scope (optional): module, package, feature (e.g. auth, api, ui)
#
# Subject rules:
#   - imperative mood ("add", not "added" or "adds")
#   - max ~72 chars
#   - no trailing period
#
# ------------------------------------------------------------
# Why:
#   Explain WHY this change is needed (problem, context).
#
# What:
#   High-level summary of WHAT changed.
#
# How:
#   Optional: implementation details if non-obvious.
#
# ------------------------------------------------------------
# Breaking Changes:
#   Describe any breaking changes here.
#
# ------------------------------------------------------------
# Closes:
#   Link issues (e.g. Closes #123, Fixes #456)
#
# ------------------------------------------------------------
# Co-authored-by:
#   Name <email>
